-- Mechel, Norilsk, Razgulay, Rosneft May Move Today: Russian Equity Preview
-- Anastasia Ustinova
-- 2010-07-21T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/mechel-norilsk-razgulay-rosneft-may-move-today-russian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based  Micex Index  fell 0.6 percent to
1,328.71 in Moscow.  
 OAO Mechel  (MTLR RX): Russia’s biggest producer of coal for
steelmaking is scheduled to report second-quarter production
results July 21. Mechel fell 1 percent to 569.24 rubles.  
 OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Copper prices jumped the
most in three weeks after a gain in U.S. building permits
boosted demand prospects for the metal used in electrical wiring
and plumbing. Russia’s largest mining company fell 0.5 percent
to 4,832.61 rubles.  
 OAO Razgulay Group  (GRAZ RX): Wheat fell for a third
straight session after Egypt, the world’s largest buyer, shunned
U.S. supplies and bought Russian grain. The Russian grain and
sugar producer dropped 0.6 percent to 39.798 rubles.  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX) and OAO  Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Crude oil
rose for a second day after a tropical wave formed in the
Caribbean and as volume diminished on the last day of trading
August futures. Share of Rosneft, Russia’s biggest oil company,
fell 1 percent to 183.46 rubles. Lukoil shares declined 0.3
percent to 1,590.59 rubles.  
